drive Swiss bank=E2=80=99s best first-quarter profits in 15 years.=C2=A0Cat=
hie Wood  Thanks Musk for Twitter Deal Despite Tesla Stock Hit. Fisker CEO=
=E2=80=99s  Twitter Account Disappears After Musk Acquisition. Times Square=
 Plots Its Comeback, and It Looks Like Las Vegas. California woman drops ph=
one into nonflush toilet, falls in at Washington national forest.If you'd l=
ike to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, right in your in=
box, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe to Money Stuf=
f and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] Something like tha=
t. Twitter=E2=80=99s announcement says =E2=80=9Ca transaction valued at app=
roximately $44 billion=E2=80=9D; I have not yet seen a precise sources and =
uses table, though Musk seems to have $46.5 billion of commitments.[2] Don=
=E2=80=99t take that too seriously. The three possible outcomes are: (1) th=
e deal does not close, and Twitter=E2=80=99s stock drops by some uncertain =
amount; (2) the deal closes and Twitter=E2=80=99s stock turns into $54.20 a=
t some uncertain period in the future; (3) the deal is jumped and Twitter=
=E2=80=99s stock sells for some higher price. You can only infer the implie=
d probability of (2) if you already have a view on the probability of (3), =
and on the prices in (1) and (3). But, sure, on customary assumptions, 84%.=
[3] See Exhibit E to the commitment letter for a =E2=80=9Csummary of condit=
ions.=E2=80=9D[4] See Exhibit B to the commitment letter for the =E2=80=9Cs=
upplemental conditions=E2=80=9D to the margin loan, which include that =E2=
=80=9CImmediately after giving effect to the advances, the LTV Ratio (as su=
ch term is defined in the Term Sheet) shall not exceed 20%.=E2=80=9D[5] Don=
=E2=80=99t take that too seriously either. Musk owns about 172.6 million Te=
sla shares and has pledged about 88.3 million of them for other loans, leav=
ing about 84.3 million free shares. A $12.5 billion loan at a 20% loan-to-v=
alue ratio requires a pledge of $62.5 billion of stock; those 84.3 million =
shares will be worth $62.5 billion at a price of $741.60 per share. But thi=
s omits his stock options to buy tens of millions more shares, some at very=
 low exercise prices; I suspect that even in the $600s he could probably sc=
rape together enough stock to do the margin loan.[6] Bloomberg=E2=80=99s La=
ura Davison and Kaustuv Basu  point out that getting a margin loan on Tesla=
 stock to buy Twitter, instead of selling Tesla stock to buy Twitter, saves=
 Musk a lot of money in taxes.[7] Even the =E2=80=9Cspecific performance=E2=
=80=9D risk is limited to his $21 billion equity commitment, not the full $=
46 billion of the buyout.[8] There are some mild noises already: =E2=80=9CT=
hierry Breton, the EU=E2=80=99s commissioner for the internal market, told =
the Financial Times that Elon Musk must follow rules on moderating illegal =
and harmful content online after Twitter accepted the billionaire=E2=80=99s=
 $44bn takeover offer. Breton said: =E2=80=98We welcome everyone. We are op=
en but on our conditions. At least we know what to tell him: =E2=80=9CElon,=
 there are rules. You are welcome but these are our rules. It=E2=80=99s not=
 your rules which will apply here.=E2=80=9D=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D But saying =
=E2=80=9Cthe company you own has to follow the law=E2=80=9D is different fr=
om *scrutinizing and possibly rejecting a merger*.[9] If you are Tesla=E2=
=80=99s board, or a Tesla shareholder, do you think you should have any say=
 in how he navigates them? If Musk Twitter ends up being bad for Tesla=E2=
=80=99s business in China, do Tesla shareholders have any cause to complain=
? (I think my vote is no! But someone will complain.)[10] This is not inves=
tment advice, and I was pretty skeptical that Elon Musk would buy Twitter! =
Never listen to me.
