</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess it is worth saying that Elon M=
usk does not own Twitter Inc. He did not buy Twitter Inc. yesterday for $54=
.20 per share in cash. He did=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/27499334.273606/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZG=
dhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTE3NzQzL2QzMTkxOTBkZGVmYTE0YS5odG0/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2fd61791" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sign an agreement</a> yesterday t=
o buy Twitter for $54.20 in cash. That is a big step! It means=C2=A0that he=
 probably=C2=A0<em>will=C2=A0</em>end up owning Twitter within a few months=
 or so. (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27499334.=
273606/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAw=
MTE5MzEyNTIyMTE3NzQzL2QzMTkxOTBkZGVmYTE0YS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC2f=
d61791" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">The deal</a> =E2=80=9Cis expected to close in 2022=E2=80=9D=
; it might take <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27=
499334.273606/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItM=
DQtMjUvdHdpdHRlci1jZW8tc2F5cy1pdC1zLWJ1c2luZXNzLWFzLXVzdWFsLXVudGlsLW11c2st=
ZGVhbC1jbG9zZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ=
1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDI2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leX=
N0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB15fe7ae5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> up to six months</a>.) =
But he does not own it yet.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So, for instanc=
e, he cannot change anything about Twitter yet; he can=E2=80=99t change mod=
eration policies or open-source the algorithm or bring back Donald Trump, o=
r whatever you are excited or worried about,=C2=A0until the deal closes.=C2=
=A0Employees who are unhappy about Musk=E2=80=99s plans for Twitter can qui=
t, but he can=E2=80=99t fire them yet. Reuters <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27499334.273606/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb2=
0vdGVjaG5vbG9neS90d2l0dGVyLWNlby10ZWxscy1lbXBsb3llZXMtY29tcGFueS1pcy1kYXJrL=
W92ZXItZnV0dXJlLXVuZGVyLW11c2stMjAyMi0wNC0yNS8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf11=
34537" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">notes</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bret =
Taylor, chair of Twitter's board of directors, aimed to reassure employees =
that the agreement with Musk prioritized "operating continuity" until the d=
eal was closed.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"I think we feel very comfo=
rtable that (the deal) gives this team the ability to continue to make the =
company successful in between signing and closing the transaction," Taylor =
said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On that same employee ca=
ll,=C2=A0CEO Parag Agrawal said =E2=80=9COnce the deal closes, we don't kno=
w which direction the platform will go.=E2=80=9D Twitter =E2=80=94=C2=A0Agr=
awal and his team and the board =E2=80=94=C2=A0are in charge of Twitter fro=
m now until the deal closes, with little or no meddling by Musk, <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27499334.273606/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjUvdHdpdHRlci1jZW8tc2F=
5cy1pdC1zLWJ1c2luZXNzLWFzLXVzdWFsLXVudGlsLW11c2stZGVhbC1jbG9zZXM_Y21waWQ9Qk=
JEMDQyNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0Z=
XImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNDI2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cC15fe7ae5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> and they</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ctold employees on Monda=
y that the social network will keep operating as usual=E2=80=9D until the c=
losing. After the deal closes, it=E2=80=99s all Musk.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Why does it take so long? Well, some things need to happen betwe=
en now and when the deal closes. Most notably, Twitter=E2=80=99s shareholde=
rs have to vote on the deal. Twitter will have to write a proxy statement e=
xplaining the deal, run it by the Securities and Exchange Commission, send =
it to shareholders and give=C2=A0them some time to read it before voting; t=
his can take months. Also there are regulatory approvals =E2=80=94=C2=A0und=
er <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27499334.273606=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9lbmZvcmNlbWVudC9wcmVtZXJnZXItbm90aWZpY2F0aW9uLX=
Byb2dyYW0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7b1c01fd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
